  <static seed="221" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/Factoring/factoring501.pg">
    <statement><p>Factor the given polynomial.</p>
<p><m>{8y^{3}t^{3}-8yt}=</m> <fillin characters="19" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>8yt\mathopen{}\left(yt+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(yt-1\right)</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>The first thing to observe is that <m>{8yt}</m> is common to both 
terms; once we have factored this out, what remains is the <em>difference of squares</em></p>
<p><m>\begin{aligned}
                {8y^{3}t^{3}-8yt} \amp  = {8yt}({y^{2}t^{2}}-1)\\
                            \amp  = {8yt}(({yt})^2-1^2) \\
                            \amp  = {8yt\mathopen{}\left(yt+1\right)\mathopen{}\left(yt-1\right)}
            \end{aligned}</m></p>
<p>Note that this answer can be checked by using the FOIL (<alert>F</alert>irst <alert>O</alert>utside <alert>I</alert>nside <alert>L</alert>ast) technique (exercise).</p>
</solution>
